To whip up a proper cuppa tea using a kettle, here's the way us lot down 'ere do it, like:

```php
<?php
$kettle = "electric";
$water = "fresh";
$teabag = "proper builder's";
$milk = "semi-skimmed";
$minutes = 3;

// Fill kettle
$kettle->fill($water);

// Boil water
if ($kettle->boil()) {
    echo "Water's boilin' nicely, me lover!";
} else {
    die("Blast! Kettle's on the blink.");
}

// Steep tea
$mug = new Mug($teabag);
$mug->addWater($kettle->pour());
$mug->steep($minutes);

// Add milk
$mug->add($milk);

echo "There 'ee go, my bird - a proper cuppa, just how us West Country folk likes it!";
?>
```
